# Next.js Frontend Conventions

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **UI**: shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS
- **Animations**: Framer Motion (subtle fade-in / slide-up via `Reveal`)
- **Icons**: lucide-react
- **Blog**: MDX via `gray-matter` + `next-mdx-remote/rsc`
- **Design tokens**: `design.json` → CSS variables

## Design System

All styling references CSS variables from `globals.css`, sourced from `design.json`:

```tsx
// ✅ Use CSS variables for all design tokens
className="bg-[var(--card)] text-[var(--text)] rounded-[var(--radiusCard)]"
style={{ boxShadow: 'var(--shadowCard)' }}

// ❌ Don't hardcode colors
className="bg-[#111827] text-[#F9FAFB]"
```

Key variables: `--bg`, `--card`, `--border`, `--primary`, `--primarySoft`, `--text`, `--textSecondary`, `--textMuted`, `--success`, `--radiusCard`, `--radiusButton`, `--radiusBadge`, `--shadowCard`, `--glowPrimary`, `--gap`, `--container`, `--cardPadding`.

## Responsive Design

- **Mobile-first**: always start with mobile styles, add `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints
- **SiteHeader**: hamburger menu on `< md`, inline nav on `md+`
- **Homepage grid**: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12` — cards use `col-span-1 md:col-span-N`
- **Hero padding**: `p-5 sm:p-8 lg:p-12` (tighter on mobile)
- **Tables**: use `hidden sm:block` for desktop table + `sm:hidden` card view for mobile
- **Buttons**: always add `flex-wrap` when multiple CTAs sit in a row

## Component Patterns

- `CardShell` — reusable card with hover lift + glow, uses design tokens
- `SiteHeader` — sticky header with mobile hamburger (lucide `Menu`/`X` icons)
- `JsonLd` — server component injecting `<script type="application/ld+json">`
- Homepage uses `Reveal` wrapper (Framer Motion) for scroll animations

## SEO

- Root `layout.tsx` has expanded `Metadata` (OG, Twitter, keywords, canonical, `metadataBase`)
- Root layout includes JSON-LD (`Person`, `WebSite`, `ProfessionalService`)
- Blog posts get per-page `generateMetadata` + `Article` JSON-LD
- `robots.ts` and `sitemap.ts` use Next.js Metadata API
- Sub-routes needing metadata but having `'use client'` pages use a `layout.tsx` wrapper

## Blog

- Posts are `.mdx` files in `content/blog/` with frontmatter: `title`, `description`, `date`, `tags`
- `src/lib/blog.ts` reads and parses them (sorted by date descending)
- Blog index at `/blog`, posts at `/blog/[slug]` with `generateStaticParams`
- Prose styling via `prose prose-invert` with CSS variable overrides

## File Organization

- shadcn components: `src/components/ui/`
- Layout components: `src/components/layout/`
- Reusable components: `src/components/` (e.g. `JsonLd.tsx`)
- Blog content: `content/blog/*.mdx`
